Output

resTsv <- "outs/WHV_10X.SCSM_fit.ss.tsv"

Loading data

knownCellAnnFile <- "../180_SCSM_subjects/WHV_10X.SCSM_HLA_fit.tsv"
mf <- SCSMMultFits()

analysisIds <- c( "ss", "vs", "smallSs", "smallVs" )
for( analysisId in analysisIds ) {
  resFile <- paste0( "outs/WHV_10X.SCSM_fit.", analysisId, ".rds" )
  
  l <- readRDS( resFile )
  l$fits$bestFitJ <- head( names( l$fits$singleFits ), 1L )
  l$fits$scsm <- l$scsm
  mf <- addFits( mf, analysisId, l$fits )
}

Visualisation of ELBO maximisation over different runs and parameters

The process maximizes ELBO (Empirical Lower BOund). Different initial conditions lead to different final fits. The one with maximal ELBO is chosen for final cell-subject mapping.

elbosPlot( mf, alignLast = FALSE )

Calling from best runs

mcll <- calcCalls( mf, modelDoublets = TRUE, minProbRatio = 1.1, doubletFrac = 0.02 )

Called subjects counts

sortedSs <- mf$fits$ss$scsm$sAnn$origS
csCountPlot( mcll, Ss = sortedSs )

Comparisons of subject calls between two run modes

callConfusionsPlot( mcll$calls$smallSs, mcll$calls$ss, Ss = NULL )

Comparisons of subject calls to the previous result

knownCAnn <- read_tsv( knownCellAnnFile ) %>% 
  mutate( calledS = factor( calledS, levels = c( "H1", "04i", "doublet" ) ) )
d <- mcll$calls$ss$piCalls %>% 
  select( p, c, calledS, status, isSinglet, isDoublet ) %>% 
  mutate( calledS = fct_recode( calledS, H1 = "SID01", `04i` = "SID02" ) )
dd <- full_join(
  d %>% select( p, c, calledS ),
  knownCAnn %>% select( p, c, oldCalledS = calledS ),
  by = c( "p", "c" )
)

Final summary table:

  • rows correspond to subjects assigned in the new analysis
  • columns - the old analysis
  • counts - the number of cells assigned to a particular subject in the new and in the old analysis
  • NAs represent those cells which are generated in one analysis (alignment) but not in the other

Majority of the cells (the diagonal) has its assignment unchanged. A number of cells is no longer recognized as doublet (3rd column).

dd %>% count( calledS, oldCalledS ) %>% 
  spread( oldCalledS, n, fill = 0L )

Write final result

write_csv( d, file = resTsv )
